/// The following commands are what I used to get the install to work on my Windows 11 laptop. I modified them from the official Solana install information https://docs.solana.com/cli/install-solana-cli-tools

/// Make sure you are running CMD as an administrator.  

curl https://release.solana.com/stable/solana-install-init-x86_64-pc-windows-msvc.exe --output C:\solana-install-tmp\solana-install-init.exe --create-dirs

C:\solana-install-tmp\solana-install-init.exe stable

/// Solana should now be installed, verify by entring the following command

solana --version


///Install rust.  I used the website
https://www.rust-lang.org/tools/install

///once rust is installed run the following command in the CLI (It can take a while for it to finish)
cargo install spl-token-cli

///once it finishes you may need to close and re-open Command prompt, then run the following to confirm it is working
spl-token --version

///All set!  Happy building!
